  "detailed_description": "This video offers an exclusive tour of the Samuel Field Mansion in Milwaukee, built in 1890 and meticulously restored to its original period. The owner invested over $2 million to preserve its historical integrity, including disassembling and rebuilding the house stone by stone in 1928. The tour highlights exquisite architectural details, gleaming wood paneling, ornate fireplaces, period-appropriate tiling, and unique features like leaded glass windows and an original air-way system integrated into the crown molding. It showcases the grand living spaces, a professionally restored kitchen, luxurious bedrooms with en-suite bathrooms, a massive ballroom, and a historically themed basement, all meticulously maintained to reflect its opulent past.",
